Ques- Given an integer n, return a counter function. This counter function initially returns n and then returns 1 more than the previous value every subsequent time it is called (n, n + 1, n + 2, etc).

Code-

var createCounter = function(n) {
    
    return function() {
        return n++;
        
    };
};



Logic-
You have to make a function - createCounter(n)
What it does?
-It returns a function
-Whenever this function call:
   - !st Time - n
   - 2nd Time - n+1
   - 3rd Time - n+2 & so on..
-It always remember last number- This is called Closure

Initial n = 10

counter() → 10 → n becomes 11
counter() → 11 → n becomes 12
counter() → 12 → n becomes 13
